transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra at Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: The newest Viagra is Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: That's what I ordered online here and I just got my prescription. That's not—it's just—

Speaker 2: It's not what I ordered.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir.

Speaker 2: So let's take a look at your prescription on my end and at the pill bottles that you have in your hand.

Speaker 1: And let's see what you received. Could I get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: We, uh, well you got it under Michael Midget, M-I-D-G-E-T-T.

Speaker 1: 2-1-8-5-5?

Speaker 2: Okay, Mike. So I see on my end what was ordered online should have been the Viagra AGV 50 milligrams, quantity of 40.

Speaker 1: Do you have that pill bottle in front of you?

Speaker 2: Could you tell me what's on the bottom right of that white label? Does it say Apco or does it say Greenstone?

Speaker 1: Broccoli?

Speaker 2: It says Apco. Okay, that was my concern.

Speaker 1: Okay, so it looks like the pharmacy went to filling disorder. They mixed up the RX numbers.

Speaker 2: Go Go Meds, they deal with generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: They deal with AGV and they also deal with the name brand Viagra, the blue pill.

Speaker 2: So on occasion they will mix these up.

Speaker 1: What I'm going to do is I'm going to send you replacements of the Viagra AGV. So this will be what you ordered.

Speaker 2: What you can expect on that will be Greenstone. Where yours says Apco, it will say Greenstone, and that's the laboratory from France.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay.

Speaker 2: It will also say AGV on the bottle, and the pills themselves will have a number 50 on it rather than a generic code.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you can do whatever you like with them. There's nothing wrong with them; they're just not the AGV.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I appreciate the help, man. What can I expect?

Speaker 1: Uh, two to five business days.

Speaker 2: Oh, perfect. Thank you, man.

Speaker 1: Yep. Thank you.
